'''Fellowship of the Academy of Medical Sciences''' ('''FMedSci''')  is an award for medical scientists who are recognised by the [[Academy of Medical Sciences, United Kingdom|Academy of Medical Sciences]] for the "excellence of their science, their contribution to medicine and society and the range of their achievements".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acmedsci.ac.uk/fellows/|title=Fellows: Academy of Medical Sciences|location=London|author=Anon|year=2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304173640/http://www.acmedsci.ac.uk/fellows/|archivedate=2016-03-04|website=acmedsci.ac.uk|publisher=Academy of Medical Sciences}}</ref>

==Fellowship==
Fellows are entitled to use the [[post-nominal letters]] '''FMedSci''';<ref name=Owens2006>{{cite journal|last1=Owens|first1=Joanna|title=Simon Campbell CBE, FMedSci, FRS|journal=[[Nature Reviews Drug Discovery]]|volume=5|issue=8|year=2006|pages=626–626|pmid=16918018|doi=10.1038/nrd2116}}</ref> see [[:Category:Fellows of the Academy of Medical Sciences]] for examples of fellows.

